cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.MM 

The paper deals with evaluating the quality of non-rigid registration algorithms for sets of images, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method proposed involves building statistical models of appearance variation across the set of images, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also mentions the use of 3D MR brain data, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
